Note: ============================================================================
Note: ERLANG TRANSLATION TESTS - Production Translation Test Suite
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Comprehensive tests for Erlang lexer, parser, translator, generator, emitter
Note: Tests: tokenization, parsing, Erlang→HIR, HIR→Erlang, round-trip
Note: ============================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/erlang/erlang_lexer.runa" as ErlangLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/erlang/erlang_parser.runa" as ErlangParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/erlang/erlang_to_hir.runa" as ErlangToHir
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/erlang/hir_to_erlang.runa" as HirToErlang
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/erlang/erlang_emitter.runa" as ErlangEmitter
Note: ============================================================================
Note: TEST FRAMEWORK
Note: ============================================================================

Type called "TestResult":
    test_name as String
    passed as Boolean
    error_message as String
End Type

Note: Local stand-ins for the HIR module/function records the erlang_to_hir
Note: translator returns. The canonical HIR types live in hir.runa but use
Note: opaque HIRNode + child-list traversal; until the test pipeline is
Note: rewritten against that idiom these local types let the test bodies
Note: compile against the schema they expect.
Type called "HIRModuleRecord":
    functions as List[HIRFunctionRecord]
End Type

Type called "HIRFunctionRecord":
    name as String
    body as Integer
End Type

Type called "TestSuite":
    suite_name as String
    results as List[TestResult]
    passed_count as Integer
    failed_count as Integer
End Type

Process called "create_test_suite" that takes name as String returns TestSuite:
    Return a value of type TestSuite with
        suite_name as name,
        results as a list containing nothing,
        passed_count as 0,
        failed_count as 0
End Process

Process called "add_test_result" that takes suite as TestSuite, result as TestResult returns Nothing:
    Add result to end of suite.results

    If result.passed:
        Set suite.passed_count to suite.passed_count plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Set suite.failed_count to suite.failed_count plus 1
    End If
End Process

Process called "report_test_suite" that takes suite as TestSuite returns String:
    Let output be "=== Test Suite: "
    Set output to output joined with suite.suite_name
    Set output to output joined with " ==="
    Set output to output joined with newline
    Set output to output joined with "Passed: "
    Set output to output joined with string representation of suite.passed_count
    Set output to output joined with ", Failed: "
    Set output to output joined with string representation of suite.failed_count
    Set output to output joined with newline

    Note: Show failed tests
    For Each result in suite.results:
        If not result.passed:
            Set output to output joined with "FAILED: "
            Set output to output joined with result.test_name
            Set output to output joined with " - "
            Set output to output joined with result.error_message
            Set output to output joined with newline
        End If
    End For

    Return output
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LEXER TESTS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_lexer_atoms" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "hello world 'quoted atom' ok error true false"

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Note: Check token count
    If length of lexer.tokens is less than 6:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Lexer Atoms",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected at least 6 tokens"
    End If

    Note: Check first token is atom
    If lexer.tokens at index 0 is not equal to TOKEN_ATOM:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Lexer Atoms",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "First token should be ATOM"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Lexer Atoms",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_lexer_variables" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "X Var _Ignored Name123"

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Note: All should be variables
    If length of lexer.tokens is less than 4:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Lexer Variables",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected at least 4 tokens"
    End If

    For Each token in lexer.tokens:
        If token is not equal to TOKEN_VARIABLE and token is not equal to TOKEN_EOF:
            Return a value of type TestResult with
                test_name as "Lexer Variables",
                passed as false,
                error_message as "All tokens should be VARIABLE"
        End If
    End For

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Lexer Variables",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_lexer_numbers" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "123 3.14 16#FF 2#1010 8#77"

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Note: Check we have number tokens
    If length of lexer.tokens is less than 5:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Lexer Numbers",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected at least 5 tokens"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Lexer Numbers",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_lexer_operators" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "+ - * / == =:= =/= ! -> =>"

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Note: Check we have operator tokens
    If length of lexer.tokens is less than 8:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Lexer Operators",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected at least 8 tokens"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Lexer Operators",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_lexer_binary_syntax" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "<< 1, 2, 3 >>"

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Note: Check for binary tokens
    If lexer.tokens at index 0 is not equal to TOKEN_LBIN:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Lexer Binary Syntax",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected TOKEN_LBIN"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Lexer Binary Syntax",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSER TESTS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_parser_simple_function" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "double(X) -> X * 2."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Note: Check function was parsed
    If length of module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Simple Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 function"
    End If

    Let func as ErlangFunction be module.functions at index 0

    If func.name is not equal to "double":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Simple Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Function name should be 'double'"
    End If

    If func.arity is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Simple Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Function arity should be 1"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Parser Simple Function",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_parser_pattern_matching" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "head([H|T]) -> H."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    If length of module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Pattern Matching",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 function"
    End If

    Let func as ErlangFunction be module.functions at index 0
    Let clause be func.clauses at index 0

    Note: Check pattern is list
    If length of clause.patterns is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Pattern Matching",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 pattern"
    End If

    Let pattern be clause.patterns at index 0

    If pattern.expr_type is not equal to "list":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Pattern Matching",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Pattern should be list"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Parser Pattern Matching",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_parser_guards" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "max(X, Y) when X > Y -> X; max(_, Y) -> Y."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    If length of module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Guards",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 function"
    End If

    Let func as ErlangFunction be module.functions at index 0

    Note: Should have 2 clauses
    If length of func.clauses is not equal to 2:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Guards",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 2 clauses"
    End If

    Let clause1 be func.clauses at index 0

    Note: First clause should have guards
    If length of clause1.guards is equal to 0:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Guards",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "First clause should have guards"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Parser Guards",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_parser_case_expression" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "test(X) -> case X of 0 -> zero; _ -> other end."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    If length of module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Case Expression",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 function"
    End If

    Let func as ErlangFunction be module.functions at index 0
    Let clause be func.clauses at index 0
    Let body_expr be clause.body at index 0

    If body_expr.expr_type is not equal to "case":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Case Expression",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Body should be case expression"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Parser Case Expression",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_parser_receive_block" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "loop() -> receive stop -> ok; {msg, M} -> io:format(M), loop() after 5000 -> timeout end."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    If length of module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Receive Block",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 function"
    End If

    Let func as ErlangFunction be module.functions at index 0
    Let clause be func.clauses at index 0
    Let body_expr be clause.body at index 0

    If body_expr.expr_type is not equal to "receive":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Receive Block",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Body should be receive expression"
    End If

    Note: Check for after clause
    If body_expr.expr_data at key "after_timeout" is equal to 0:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser Receive Block",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Receive should have after clause"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Parser Receive Block",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_parser_list_comprehension" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "doubles(L) -> [X * 2 || X <- L]."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    If length of module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser List Comprehension",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 function"
    End If

    Let func as ErlangFunction be module.functions at index 0
    Let clause be func.clauses at index 0
    Let body_expr be clause.body at index 0

    If body_expr.expr_type is not equal to "list_comprehension":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Parser List Comprehension",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Body should be list comprehension"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Parser List Comprehension",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TRANSLATOR TESTS (Erlang → HIR)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_translator_basic_function" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "double(X) -> X * 2."

    Note: Lex and parse
    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let erl_module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Note: Translate to HIR
    Let hir_module as HIRModuleRecord be translate_erlang_to_hir with erl_module

    Note: Check HIR function was created
    If length of hir_module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Translator Basic Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 HIR function"
    End If

    Let hir_func as HIRFunctionRecord be hir_module.functions at index 0

    If hir_func.name is not equal to "double":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Translator Basic Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "HIR function name should be 'double'"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Translator Basic Function",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_translator_message_passing" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "send_msg(Pid, Msg) -> Pid ! Msg."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let erl_module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Let hir_module as HIRModuleRecord be translate_erlang_to_hir with erl_module

    If length of hir_module.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Translator Message Passing",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Expected 1 HIR function"
    End If

    Note: Check body contains send operation
    Let hir_func as HIRFunctionRecord be hir_module.functions at index 0

    If length of hir_func.body is equal to 0:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Translator Message Passing",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "HIR function should have body"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Translator Message Passing",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GENERATOR TESTS (HIR → Erlang)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_generator_basic_function" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "double(X) -> X * 2."

    Note: Full pipeline: Erlang → HIR → Erlang
    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let erl_module1 be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Let hir_module as HIRModuleRecord be translate_erlang_to_hir with erl_module1

    Let erl_module2 be generate_erlang_from_hir with hir_module

    Note: Check generated module has function
    If length of erl_module2.functions is not equal to 1:
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Generator Basic Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Generated module should have 1 function"
    End If

    Let func as ErlangFunction be erl_module2.functions at index 0

    If func.name is not equal to "double":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Generator Basic Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Generated function name should be 'double'"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Generator Basic Function",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: EMITTER TESTS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_emitter_module" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "-module(test). -export([double/1]). double(X) -> X * 2."

    Note: Parse and emit
    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Let output be emit_erlang_module with module

    Note: Check output contains module name
    If not output contains "test":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Emitter Module",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Output should contain module name"
    End If

    Note: Check output contains function
    If not output contains "double":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Emitter Module",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Output should contain function name"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Emitter Module",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ROUND-TRIP TESTS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_roundtrip_simple_function" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "double(X) -> X * 2."

    Note: Round-trip: Erlang → HIR → Erlang → Text
    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module1 be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Let hir_module as HIRModuleRecord be translate_erlang_to_hir with module1

    Let module2 be generate_erlang_from_hir with hir_module

    Let output be emit_erlang_module with module2

    Note: Check output is valid Erlang
    If not output contains "double":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Round-Trip Simple Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Output should contain 'double'"
    End If

    If not output contains "->":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Round-Trip Simple Function",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Output should contain '->'"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Round-Trip Simple Function",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_roundtrip_pattern_matching" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "head([H|_]) -> H."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module1 be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Let hir_module as HIRModuleRecord be translate_erlang_to_hir with module1

    Let module2 be generate_erlang_from_hir with hir_module

    Let output be emit_erlang_module with module2

    Note: Check output contains list pattern
    If not output contains "head":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Round-Trip Pattern Matching",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Output should contain 'head'"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Round-Trip Pattern Matching",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INTEGRATION TESTS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_integration_factorial" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "factorial(0) -> 1; factorial(N) when N > 0 -> N * factorial(N - 1)."

    Note: Complete pipeline
    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module1 be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Let hir_module as HIRModuleRecord be translate_erlang_to_hir with module1

    Let module2 be generate_erlang_from_hir with hir_module

    Let output be emit_erlang_module with module2

    Note: Check recursive function preserved
    If not output contains "factorial":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Integration Factorial",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Output should contain 'factorial'"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Integration Factorial",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Process called "test_integration_actor_model" returns TestResult:
    Let input be "loop() -> receive {get, Pid} -> Pid ! {value, 42}, loop(); stop -> ok end."

    Let lexer be create_lexer with input
    Call lex with lexer

    Let parser be create_erlang_parser with lexer.tokens, lexer.lexemes, lexer.lines
    Let module1 be parse_erlang_module with parser

    Let hir_module as HIRModuleRecord be translate_erlang_to_hir with module1

    Let module2 be generate_erlang_from_hir with hir_module

    Let output be emit_erlang_module with module2

    Note: Check actor pattern preserved
    If not output contains "receive":
        Return a value of type TestResult with
            test_name as "Integration Actor Model",
            passed as false,
            error_message as "Output should contain 'receive'"
    End If

    Return a value of type TestResult with
        test_name as "Integration Actor Model",
        passed as true,
        error_message as ""
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TEST RUNNER
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "run_erlang_tests" returns TestSuite:
    Let suite be create_test_suite with "Erlang Translation System"

    Note: Run lexer tests
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_lexer_atoms
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_lexer_variables
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_lexer_numbers
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_lexer_operators
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_lexer_binary_syntax

    Note: Run parser tests
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_parser_simple_function
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_parser_pattern_matching
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_parser_guards
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_parser_case_expression
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_parser_receive_block
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_parser_list_comprehension

    Note: Run translator tests
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_translator_basic_function
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_translator_message_passing

    Note: Run generator tests
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_generator_basic_function

    Note: Run emitter tests
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_emitter_module

    Note: Run round-trip tests
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_roundtrip_simple_function
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_roundtrip_pattern_matching

    Note: Run integration tests
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_integration_factorial
    Call add_test_result with suite and test_integration_actor_model

    Return suite
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MAIN ENTRY POINT
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Nothing:
    Let suite be run_erlang_tests

    Let report be report_test_suite with suite

    Note: Print report (simplified - in production would use IO)
    Note: Report output would be displayed here
End Process
